oc:kn_10611036 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting hooks from signal data" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Rank personalization hooks by: (1) Recency — last 7-14 days, (2) Specificity — a concrete action they took, not a general trend, (3) Relevance — connects to a value your product delivers." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Recent, specific, relevant hooks produce dramatically higher response rates than generic or stale references." .

oc:kn_3d87429b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When Common Room returns minimal data on the target" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When signal data is sparse, do NOT draft outreach. Run web search first. If still sparse, present only real data found and ask the user for context." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Asking the user for context yields better outreach than fabricating personalization from thin signals." .

oc:kn_400aa1d7 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating the LinkedIn format" ;
    oc:directiveContent "LinkedIn messages must be under 300 characters with no exceptions. No attachments or links in the first message. No pitch." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Platform character limits and social norms require brevity. Pitching in first LinkedIn messages reduces response rates." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_57fd8ca1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating outreach output" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always produce all three formats (email, call script, LinkedIn) clearly labeled, plus a Signal Notes section explaining which signals were used and why." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Providing all three formats gives the user channel flexibility and ensures consistent messaging across touchpoints." .

oc:kn_5a8a5779 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any outreach format" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never start messages with filler ('I hope this email finds you well'), defensive language ('I know you're busy but...'), vague subject lines ('Following up'), or fabricated familiarity." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These patterns signal generic mass outreach and immediately disengage the recipient." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_8b0cefcb a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating the email format" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Email must be 3-5 sentences max with a single specific low-friction ask. No paragraphs." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Long emails get skimmed or ignored. A single clear ask dramatically increases response rates." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_9222b316 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating the call script format" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The call script must be speakable naturally — mentally read it aloud to check rhythm. It is a guide, not a word-for-word read: Opening (10-15s), Value Bridge (20-30s), Ask (10s)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Call scripts that sound stilted when spoken aloud will not be used by sales reps and sound inauthentic to prospects." .

oc:kn_b274b8f1 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When calibrating message tone for any format" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Match tone to context: warm and collaborative for inbound/community signals; professional and brief for cold outreach; formal and outcome-focused for executives; casual and low-pressure for re-engagement." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Tone mismatch signals that the sender doesn't understand the recipient's context or relationship stage." .

oc:kn_ced3ed62 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When drafting any outreach message" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never fabricate signals or personalization hooks. Only reference data actually retrieved from Common Room or web search." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Outreach grounded in fabricated signals is worse than no outreach — it erodes trust and credibility irreparably." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

